  "text": "For osteoblast differentiation, bone marrow cultures were established in a basal medium supplemented with 0.2 mM ascorbic acid and 10 mM β-glycerophosphate and maintained for 28 days with half the medium changed every 6 days [CITATION_1] . On day 10, the medium was supplemented with either netoglitazone or rosiglitazone at the concentrations described above, and the treatments were repeated with each medium change, for the duration of the experiment. Colony Forming Units for Osteoblasts (CFU-OB) were detected by Von Kossa staining of mineral and enumerated as described [CITATION_2] .",
